					<div class="w3about-text"> 
                       <p>One of the common problems which is associated with surgeries is hypothermia. It causes a significant drop in the body temperature of patients before, after, and during surgery. It happens due to prolonged exposure to cold temperatures and anxiety among patients. Well, high-tech inventions in the healthcare sector have enabled medical experts to meet patients’ expectations. Wallabies Warm Care is offering top-quality patient forced air warming blankets to hospitals and nursing homes in Ontario, Canada. These are the warming systems that use a heating unit and blanket for the prevention of hypothermia among patients. These devices are clinically proven to be used for pre and post-operative patient care. </p>
<h1>Working of air warming blankets</h1>
<p>These devices are simple-to-use warming units that enable the hospitals of easy utilization for patients admitted. The device can be connected to a portable heater with a hose. It works to supply warm air surrounding the patient’s body to maintain body temperature. These tech-enabled devices have replaced the use of traditional wire and water circulation heating systems. Also, the use of these blankets provides more control against the inception of hypothermia among patients. </p>
